                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12600942" author="bien" created="Thu, 29 May 2008 22:22:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oops, misdiagnosis&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12600943" author="stack" created="Thu, 29 May 2008 22:22:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Made this blocker on 0.2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12601487" author="jimk" created="Sun, 1 Jun 2008 19:34:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, an exception is thrown. HQL for some reason does not display it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12601538" author="mbu" created="Mon, 2 Jun 2008 06:59:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-627&quot; title=&quot;Disable table doesn&amp;#39;t work reliably&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-627&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-627&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I do get an exception from addColumn, but no exception from HBaseAdmin.disableTable if the disabling for some reason didn&apos;t happen.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12601671" author="stack" created="Mon, 2 Jun 2008 16:46:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mr. Firby was burned by this over the w/e (He couldn&apos;t figure how to drop a table)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12601695" author="bien" created="Mon, 2 Jun 2008 18:19:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is broken for dropTable, not for addColumnFamily.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12603288" author="stack" created="Sat, 7 Jun 2008 05:26:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Made a fix in branch.  HQL was going out of its way to parse the exception message dropping the actual exception type.  After HQL was done w/ its parse, all that was left was name of table.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
durruti:~/Documents/checkouts/hbase/branches/0.1 stack$ ./bin/hbase shell
Hbase Shell, 0.0.2 version.
Copyright (c) 2007 by udanax, licensed to Apache Software Foundation.
Type &apos;help;&apos; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; usage.

hql &amp;gt; create table &apos;x&apos; (&apos;x&apos;)
  --&amp;gt; ;
Creating table... Please wait.
Table created successfully.
hql &amp;gt; drop table &apos;x&apos;;
Dropping x... Please wait.
 You must first disable table &amp;lt;x&amp;gt; before you can drop it
hql &amp;gt; disable &apos;x&apos;;
08/06/06 22:25:03 INFO hbase.HBaseAdmin: Disabled table x
Table disabled successfully. (10.03 sec)
hql &amp;gt; drop table &apos;x&apos;;
Dropping x... Please wait.
08/06/06 22:25:06 INFO hbase.HBaseAdmin: table x deleted
1 table(s) dropped successfully. (0.03 sec)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is how it now works in branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12606150" author="stack" created="Wed, 18 Jun 2008 23:51:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Trunk throws a big dirty, explanatory exception if you try drop a non-disabled table:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
